You are working in the `lightbox-js` repository.

Project context:
- This is a small, dependency-free lightbox library.
- Main runtime file: `index.js`
- Demo page: `index.html`
- Styles: `style/index.css`

Code style and constraints:
- Use plain JavaScript (ES modules), no new runtime dependencies.
- Preserve public API behavior:
  - `open(data)`
  - `setGallery(list)`
  - `openGalleryItem(i)`
- Keep changes minimal and focused; avoid broad refactors unless requested.
- Prefer readable, explicit logic over clever abstractions.
- Keep browser compatibility reasonable for modern browsers.

When editing:
- Fix root causes, not only symptoms.
- Keep UI state transitions consistent when switching media types.
- Avoid breaking existing demo behavior in `index.html`.
- If changing behavior, update `README.md` examples/docs accordingly.

Validation checklist:
- No syntax errors.
- Image mode still supports rotate/zoom/reset + pan.
- Non-image modes hide image-only controls.
- Gallery mode still opens and selects items correctly.
